{
  "texts": [
    "In Sect. 5 we discuss the details of our Bayesian RD analysis and collect the parameter estimation (PE) results on GWTC-3, comparing them with the results obtained by the LVK Collaboration, both in the IMR and RD regimes.",
    "We also describe our procedure to robustly search for HMs, including the systematic uncertainty in the ringdown starting time.",
    "In Sect. 6, we introduce fractional shifts in the QNMs spectrum to study potential deviations from GR in the RD, discussing in detail tests of the final state conjecture under the assumption of the presence of two angular modes.",
    "We conclude and discuss future prospects in Sect. 7.",
    "Ringdown modelsThe linear gravitational perturbations of a Kerr BH are described by the Teukolsky equation [84,85], with the main GW emission component captured byh + -ih × = M d L lm h lm Y lm (ι, ϕ),h lm ≡ A 0,lm e -σ lm (t-t 0)+iφ 0,lm, (where M ≡ m 1 +m 2 is the total initial mass of the binary, d L is the luminosity distance, Y lmn are spin-weighted spherical harmonics (SWSH)."
  ]
}